  <CalDefinition Description="There shall be multiple pairs of configurable thresholds used to classify the results. Each domain based SLM shall have its own threshold pair. The combined SLM used at the highest level of the user interface shall have its own pair of thresholds. Additionally  there shall be a threshold for critical commands. This critical command threshold shall be configurable for commands whose action it deemed to be difficult to reverse  thus  the system shall be more cautious about acting on it." Name="EMBEDDED_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD_ARRAY_MEXICANSPANISH" References="GIS-696" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_cFpTsH8qEeWMmJGlhCyCXg</CalID>
    <Type>IntegerArray</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>10/30/2015</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of a new CAL, CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD_ARRAY_MEXICO_SPANISH CAL, that was confirmed to be needed.</Description>
      <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>3/7/2016</Date>
      <Description>Changed the name of this CAL from CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD_ARRAY_MEXICO_SPANISH to EMBEDDED_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD_ARRAY_MEXICANSPANISH to also include the word EMBEDDED at the beginning of the CAL name to make it easier to distinquish between the embedded and new server speech recognition CALs being added within this caldef file for MY18.  Also, updated some of the default values within this calibration array.</Description>
      <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
