  <CalDefinition Description="The period of time  after the&#xA;outgoing prompt  during which the system is accepting&#xA;audio input for recognition is called the listening&#xA;window.&#xA;In the event that a user doesn&#x92;t speak during the listening&#xA;window  the speech recognition process terminates&#xA;after a configurable period of time. The system reprompts&#xA;the user for the same input.&#xA;&#xA;No Speech Timeout" Name="NOSPEECHTIMEOUT" References="GIS-696" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_yrT3eE1AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
